snippet: While the two tornadoes that hit Breezy Point, Queens, and Canarsie, Brooklyn, caused no serious injuries, property owners had plenty of debris to throw out.
abstract: Residents of Canarsie, Brooklyn and Breezy Point, Queens, clean up after two tornadoes touch down in the boroughs, causing no series injuries or widespread damage; National Weather Service records just 10 tornadoes in New York City from 1950 through 2010.
lead_paragraph: While the two tornadoes that hit Breezy Point, Queens, and Canarsie, Brooklyn, caused no serious injuries, property owners had plenty of debris to throw out.
